    "where Z θ = ∫ e -f θ (x) dx is normalizing constant.",
    "This also ensures that p θ (x) is a density function.",
    "Since Z θ being a constant, thus ∇ x log Z θ equals zero.",
    "Therefore, Score-Based Models are not related to normalization terms, which greatly expands the range of models or architectures that can be used.",
    "Similar to other explicit generative models, Score-Based Models can calculate the Fisher divergence between the predicted distribution of the model and the ground-truth data distribution to measure the difference between the two distributions."
